<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="71cd6057f09b34426d1aced53249d173" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/heroclix/treports/treports.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/vs/treports/treports.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/treports/treports.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Essen Premier<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=12149'>Patrick "CaptCanada" Malboeuf</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=12149&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> October 24, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> This is the follow up to my last tournament report about the week I spent in Essen. This part is dedicated to the Premier Event Essen 2002 and it&#39;s long.<br />
<br />
Let&#39;s begin this tournament report by a funny fact. After we Canada had lost to Germany in day 3 of the World Cup, I was looking at the remaining games of the World Cup to try to understand the general meta when I met Benoit a French guy who realized that we both spoke french. Immediately we began talking, he asked me how I did at the World Cup, I told him and he started asking question about what I thought would be the best choice for the next day at the premier. He seemed to be surprised by my prepared answer. I told him that Moria was the number one choice for a day one at any premier event. Then he asked me more and more questions and I ended up showing him my deck and explaining the strategy to him. His friend Gregory Denis met us and asked some questions but said less. He seemed confident enough about his choice (I would later find out who that guy was and the fact that he finished 2nd at the continentals or something like that).<br />
<br />
So the next morning I arrive at the convention center with the exact same deck as the day before that I had gone 2-0 with and I meet Benoit who says they playtested my deck between themselves. He says it&#39;s a killer, but that you have to play it well for it to really work. I agree with him so he tells me that he has chosen another deck with nazgul shadow. We talk a little, he asks me how confident I feel, I tell him: I told you, Moria will get you to day 2 guaranteed. So we laugh a little and the whole thing starts.<br />
<br />
Bam! 135 people. It was crazy, you could barely find a place to stand up, people were crowding the convention like hell and there were those drums and backpipes all the time that just made it a circus. I begin my first game stressed, as I always begin my first games of a tournament. Confidence is progressive for me.<br />
<br />
Round 1: A belgian Guy. (Again sorry for forgetting all you peoples names...)<br />
<br />
My brother&#39;s moria v.s. Legolas premium & Gimli Dwarf of the mountain race start with multi culture moria/sauron/uruk.<br />
<br />
He bids more than me (I bid 1) and makes me start. My fellowship is invincible if I move once every time and so I do. My shadow is powerful enough to dissuade him to double move. The game ends up being very close as he double moves and stops at 7. There is 2 minutes left in the game, so it will go to time and I hate time. So, I play very fast a bunch of companions and then my opponent realizes that I played 10 companions so he says, you played 10 companions, that&#39;s illegal and looks at me as if I loose the game because of that, so he calls a judge and Dan arrives. He gives me a warning and writes it on my sheet, saying that another one will give me a loss and the opponent seems very upset. Seems like he would have been satisfied with me loosing the game because I played 10 companions. I take my last companion back into my hand and move with 45 seconds left in the game. I ask Dan if we have more time because of his intervention and he gives me 30 more seconds. Great. I move, he plays minions, 20 seconds left, I assign and resolve skirmishes at an incredible speed, killing everyone of my companions and then I say regroup, he&#39;s astonished by how fast things are going and with 10 seconds left I move again. Of course I survive and get the time win.<br />
<br />
At that time the drums and the clock are making me crazy. I feel like I need more time. I try to go to the bathroom but there is a huge trafic jam. Nobody&#39;s moving cause there’s too many people in the place. I just suffocate. I just want to relax.<br />
<br />
Round 2 starts: Cristoff Mueller (I think)<br />
<br />
My brother&#39;s Moria v.s. Classic ranger horn/uruk<br />
<br />
He walked sites 3 to 6 always one minion short of being overwhelmed but instead of stacking my minions, I just played them as they came because I was so stressed at the time. Worst then that, I double moved, stressed at the time and going half for a free-peoples win, half at a shadow win. Not good at all. It is then that I realized that adding foul creation was not that good of an idea since it allowed my opponents to reconcile better and made me move more because of lack of minions, making my opponent reconcile even better. It is then that I decided to use foul creation only to look at my opponent&#39;s hand or when it would be absolutely necessary. Anyways, he survived my unplanned swarm. Benoit was right. You gotta know how to play this deck. At that point it seemed like I couldnt remember the tips of my brother and that I didnt believe in my ressources.<br />
<br />
However, because we finish before time, I am able to go to the bathroom, a routine I had developped through the world cup and that allowed me to relax and some water on my face. I sat alone outside of the convention and tried to relax.<br />
<br />
I went back to the tables and met Yako and Yannick who were both 2-0 and going great. I told them how I was going, and they informed me that my time win would handicap me and would perhaps count as a loss in the day&#39;s total for determining who would advance. I asked them what that meant and they told me: &quot; that means you have to win all your games from here to go to day 2&quot;. Okay.<br />
<br />
Round 3: A german beginner<br />
<br />
Not much to say about the game if not that I was going fast because I didnt want to go to time again. I explained to him at the end of the  game that normally I didnt go so fast against new players in order to help them learn but another timed game would have gotten me out of the tournament. I won, overwhelming him at site 6 when I was at 8.<br />
<br />
Round 4: A friend of Benoit, the french guy<br />
<br />
My brother&#39;s Moria v.s. trust me/uruks<br />
<br />
He played a trust me deck and kept playing more and more companions, while gettting his sleep caradhras exactly at the right time. He double moved 7-8 easily and I didnt play anthing against his 7 companions since I was waiting for da man. I got him at 9 and was able to play: nertea, brings back enquea, etcetera. and had 4 minions on frodo. That came out of nowhere, he was doing great at 8. Nertea da man.<br />
<br />
Benoit met us at the end of the game to discuss how his friend had performed and was trying to see what mistake his friend had made and quite frankly I said I didnt think he made one. He asked me how I was doing and I told him that I would be in the top 16. Of course, I wasnt so sure but at least my consistent confidence impressed him.<br />
<br />
Round 5: Guess what, I play Benoit :)<br />
<br />
My brother&#39;s Moria v.s. ranger/nazgul<br />
<br />
When he realised that he was playing me and that I showed up, he just went sad. He asked everyone how that could be possible and of course I was paired down because I had a time win. Before we even had started, I had won. He kept saying how I would destroy him. At one moment, he tried to convince himself that he had a chance and said: if you dont get your scimitars early, I might have a chance. I drew 1 armory and a scimitar in my starting hand and he just morally conceded the game. The rest is history. I overwhelmed him. I am usually very good at the mind game, but there I didnt even need to do anything. Anyways, he was a nice guy and I hope I get to meet him again some day. Salut Benoit!<br />
<br />
I kept going back to Yako and Yannick after every round to see how they were doing and both were like 4-0 at one time. I was always a doubtful case since only one loss would put me out of the competition, but we dreamed of us 3 quebecer making the top 16th. I serioulsy had doubts about my presence. I had to win my next 3 ones and now top players would come.<br />
<br />
Round 6: The Gaffer from Belgium! (Yeah, that’s a country J )<br />
<br />
My brother&#39;s Moria v.s. Frodo.... / Moria Swarm<br />
<br />
Let me tell you something. Some people have weird ideas, but to play a frodo alone fellowship in day one of a premier event, you gotta have balls. And he was going pretty well that day. Unfortunately for him, his moria can&#39;t overwhelm 9 companions with 6 stealths and he sure wont choke a moria/elrond-ottar deck. Let&#39;s just say it wasnt his ideal matchup.<br />
<br />
He bid 4 to let me start and I single moved all my way to 9 while he couldnt double move with ... frodo. An interesting thing happened on site 2 tough when I moved and he played 2 runners and a scavengers to my frodo and Gandalf. Let&#39;s just say that I am glad I am intelligent enough to count the pool I generate and the cards I have in hand before I play anything. That stealth came out handy.<br />
<br />
Now it became interesting. I met with Yako and Yannick and learned that they had their first loss. Yannick told us about his really gay loss in a really cool way. He moved to site 2 with exhausted sam totalling 4 companions. His opponent is lucky enough to get the good pool for 2 trackers and a band of the eye. No problem there. Wait! Manoeuver he plays hate on sam. Yannick has to assign a 7 strenght on frodo and his opponent plays enduring evil! Blink Blink!, that&#39;s LOTR for you.<br />
<br />
Unfortunately for him, Yannick would be victim to the decklist ghost and get a loss that would take him out of day 2 even if he deserved to be among the top 16.<br />
<br />
Round 7 : A German if I am not mistaking,<br />
<br />
My brother’s Moria v.s. Ranger/Nazgul<br />
<br />
I don’t remember everything from the game but I do remember that he kept making mistakes like playing morgul gates after playing a nazgul and I don’t know why I felt relax so I let him but at some point I stopped allowing him take backs and he said he understood, that he was very tired and I overwhelmed him relatively easily.<br />
<br />
So there I was 6-1. I went to talk to Kyle Heuer and he said I was probably assured of being in the top 16. I didn’t like that « probably » so I really wanted to win that last one, plus it felt really good to have my number (because of the number of people.. and I suspect because fo their names matchups were announced by numbers) announced at the winner’s table, with 7 other players that were assured of making day 2. I was the only north-american at that table and it felt strange but I got to talk with the others.<br />
<br />
Then, something strange happened. I initially was paired against Chirs Schaut of the US but as soon as he saw me, he yelled JUDGE! I was so surprised then he told me they had given him a win from his last game and he had lost and signed his sheet. I have never seen a guy so anxious to get a loss writen on his score sheet. Anyways, I told him I was amazed by his honesty and he didnt say much and went to face someone else while I got a new and I must add cool opponent.<br />
<br />
That guy spoke french (I had a few french speaking opponents that day) and we talked a bit.<br />
<br />
Round 8 : That nice French Speaking guy<br />
<br />
My Brother’s Moria v.s. Ranger/… Sauron!<br />
<br />
I couldn’t believe my eyes. The guy was actually playing Sauron and had beaten a lot of people because everyone bid high. The cool thing with my deck as I said is that it is not weak against anything and doesnt rely on anything, including biding high. That seemed to make his enduring evil and hates less powerful ( he played no Ulaire Enquea) so that allowed me to walk right through Sauron’s legions. He wasnt playing the Orc Bowmen stuff but instead was playing big minions with lots of events. He even played 2 memory of many things which I had to read when I stinged him since I didnt know what it did. It proved to be annoying against me but I just kept playing one elf ally at a time. I was able to double move 7-9 and I got two minions on my frodo totalling 11 to my 6 and he didnt have any enduring evil so I won.<br />
<br />
I was very satisfied with how things had gone. I talked to some people who insured me I would be top 16, I went to the bathroom and came back and found everybody was gone and Joel was waiting for me. The convention center had closed and we had to get out.<br />
<br />
That night, there was no way I was sleeping without knowing my opponent for the next day so I went to the Internet Cafe and waited until DGMA posted the results. I was surprised at being 4 for day one but very pleased. I learned that I was playing Rolan Benn, the German guy I had beaten at day 3 world cup.<br />
<br />
I knew he was playing Boromir and Frying pan, so I immediately though of playing that moria card that prevents the player from exerting a hobbit (Throw yourself in next time I think) but I felt that card sucked and couldnt be in an efficient deck. So I went to sleep but couldnt, I kept thinking about my deck. The other thing was that I wanted to get rid of foul creation since everyone playing uruks were also paying no business of ours and since it helped the opponent cycle their hand better and pushed me to double move when I should rely more on shadow.<br />
<br />
At one moment, I kept thinking about how to kill allies with Moria and realised that it would be even better to kill that guy who brings them to fight. It would also kill a companion and thus make the swarm easier. So I thought about adding Such A little thing but I didnt like having only one since it was like having none. That is when I had the silly thought of playing 4. That would mean me never having to stack them in my hand, always getting rid of a 0 cost card in the manoeuver and preventing opponents from playing Boromir, which was in the most case their main companion. All week I had seen Boromir based decks, most often with horn so I decided I would play four of Such a little thing, removing that costly flanker, Enquea who wasnt of much help since I would kill boromir everytime and a troll since a troll doesnt overwhelm. I would thus add one shaodw and one fellowship card to make my deck 82 cards (I will later post « Anti Euro Meta » but meanwhile you can look at it on DGMA).<br />
<br />
I didn’t sleep a lot that night, but at least I was ready, really ready.<br />
<br />
Day 2<br />
<br />
I arrived pretty early at the convention center and had to wait for a while. Then at some point many people arrived amongst whom was Rolan Benn, my opponent. As soon as we saw each other, we had a smile and came to talk to each other. He really his a nice guy to talk to and there was no mind game at all, I even asked him if he was nervous, he told me he wasnt, I admitted to him that I was.<br />
<br />
So after a while the staff put a really cool setting for the day with a set of tables for the finalists separated from the rest of the tables by a red rope held with poles, with judges standing there making sure nobody came close to us but could look from afar. That set me in a serious mood right away. I knew I could beat my opponent cause I had done it twice in a row before and I had even added tech against his deck.<br />
<br />
Round 1 : Rolan Benn<br />
<br />
Anti euro-meta v.s. Ranger-Horn/Nazguls<br />
<br />
Game 1<br />
<br />
He bid high again in order to start and that was fine with me. He started and moved very fast to site 3 which was also fine with me, not letting him time to reconcile cards to set up against moria, but knowing that his shadow would not stop me. I progressively damaged him and he finally died at site 7 with the skip archery site, after I had stacked a good shadow hand for him.<br />
<br />
Game 2<br />
<br />
He bid and I bid higher because I had anticipated that he would like to let me start to have a chance. I let him begin since he had that habbit of running through site 1-3 and not setting up, which was good for me. He did that again, but a weird thing happened when he moved to 3 he said : I will move again but started reconciling. So I said to him, what are you doing? And he didnt understand at firts but realised he had just reconciled while moving. We asked a judge and he said since he has reconciled, he must not move. But I had just reconciled a Such a little thing (I had drawn none in the first game and my opponent didnt even know that I played one) and he had 1 possession so I said but I don’t want him to stay, I want him to move, like he said. The judge seemed confused ans I said : take backs are not allowed, he said he would move and I do not allow him to take back that decision. So the judge had no choice but to allow him to move, but allowed me to cards at random from my opponent’s hands, look at them and replace them on top of his draw deck. I drew 2 shadow cards so I said : « that helped him » since he could benefit from free-peoples cards he had drawn but there was nothing else we could do. That is an interesting decision because this could happen again in the future and the cards he would benefit from could be gamre changing. Fortunately enough they were not that time and I was able to kill his Boromir at site 3, which really was tough for a horn deck. The rest is history, without Boromir I was able to overwhelm him at site 5.<br />
<br />
Those games were really quick and of course boosted my confidence level. I had a lot of time, even enough to visit the convention, go to the bathroom, relax anbd talk to Kyle.<br />
<br />
I must say I never had a chance to really talk to one of Decipher’s staff but I got a chance to know Kyle a little and he sure is a nice guy. We got to talk and laugh a little as he would make jokes with decklists such as coming towards me with my decklist after my win and presenting the sheet saying : « you are missing…. No nothing man I’m just kidding » which is the best thing to say to a stressed card player on day 2 to make him have a heart attack. He kept saying how my deck was brutal, a machine and it convinced me and those who heard it so I must say part of me believing so much in my chances came from Kyle. After my first win he even said : I like your chances, I bet you’ll be in the top four. Just joking I said : Are you kidding me, I’m going back home with that (pointing at the huge 2500$ check). Finally he said to me : why dont you just win the whole thing, since I have already written your decklist, that would save me some time. Alright Kyle, I won’t do it for the moneyor the glory, but just because it will help you out J.<br />
<br />
So Bastian had finished his first round two and as he said had had the advanatge of being able to know who his opponent in first round was while his opponent didn’t. he played the sauron guy and beat him in two games. So tehy asked us if we would like to start playing and since I had had a long enough break I said yes, so we went for it.<br />
<br />
Round 2 : Bastian (who is really cool by the way).<br />
Anti Euro Meta v.s. Frodo signet companions with pipeweeds/ uruks<br />
<br />
From the start we were joking, not taking it seriously at all, before we sat down he used his big german voice and his heigh and said : I am going to kick your little north american but and I played the intimidated one but I just couldnt do it seriously, we just had to much fun. So we sit down at the table and Yannick brought Da Mascot from day 1, hsi Ghetto Yoda which is a Yoda puppet with a bandanna. Yannick ahd been our coach through World Cup and it had worked so when he made Ghetto Yoda sit down at my table and told me to rub his head, I rubbed it. The funny thing is that when Bastian saw that, he intentionally kicked under the table to make Yoda fall from it, but it magically stayed there. Ghetto Yoda rules.<br />
<br />
Game 1<br />
<br />
Bastian had heard that my fellowship was weak (something I read from some message board  groupies afterwards) from somebody else and didnt feel that confortable against moria so he bid higher and let me start. From the start, I single moved and got companions ans stealths. At site 4 I move and generate enough pool to get Saruman and two minions in my face. I exert sam poet, intuition, stealth. Thats it. At 5 I dont want to play a 5th companion but it’s pippin (who can say no to pippin, he’s the greatest) so I play him and heal sam, so again he exerts, stealth and dies. Next site I move to 6 so I have a legion of allies waiting for me. Bastian then realises that my fellowship is untouchable so he moves to 6 and I have a good shadow hand so I just take my galadriel and put it on top of my cards, as if I had to remember something about her. That is when he took her and read her text, realizing I would not loose my legion of allies (already having Boromir with horn) at next site since I would exert for the wilderland. That basically meant I would not die to his shadow, he thought about double moving but didnt. Hey, can’t bluff Bastian. Anyways, I single moved to 7 easily and Bastian knew he would have to double move once in order to have a chance and I knew it two so I played nothing at 7, reoconciling better and he went for it. Da man came out and he was one shadow short of not being overwhelmed. Guard commander did it again as Frodo and Sam fell to his power.<br />
<br />
Game 2<br />
<br />
By game 2, Bastian had realised that the rumors of my fellowship being weak were a little false. But nevertheless, I wanted to see of that fellowship did against moria (I mean choke and pipeweed? Come on!). Surprinsigly enough he just was going through my orcs like butter. He drew sleep caradhras exactly at the right times, played betrayal of isengard which is an annoyance and kept healing his archers (legolas and aragorn) every time with pipes. It’s like facing 5 directed archery every turn agains 1 vitality orcs! So I began not playing any orcs and stacking a hand for site 7 (skip archery) since I knew he wasnt playing anything to change the site. Then he arrived there and of course could do nothing.<br />
<br />
One cool thing was that throughout the tournament some guy kept taking pictures of games and every game I playhed he went back at the end to take a picture of my swarms, that helped me since I wanted to make the biggest swarm possible each time so it would be on the internet or something. My biggest one for the day was 13 minions, including you guessed it : da man.<br />
<br />
After the games, me Bastian and Kyle got to talk and that is when I realised that my deck was kicking butts. At that point, when Bastian said : I want the guy that won against me to win the whole thing so I can say I lost against the best, I just got convinced that I would win the whole thing. Funny how confidence can be a frivolous thing, in my case that was a very important turning point in the day.<br />
<br />
My third matchup was done way later that day since the guy that finished 3rd was my next pairing and since that guy plays sooooooo sloooooow. In day one, when his game went to time against another top player (the one that finished with no loss except for his decklist error) he was at site 8 like his opponent, but had 3 burdens while his opponent had 2. The time was over so he was in the skirmish phase and it would stop at the regroup so he was sure of having a time loss. But he kept thinking (and I mean thinking) about how to assign the troll. He took about 10 freakin minutes to finally assign him to Aragorn with armor. The judge watching the game saw of ridiculous it was and kept asking his opponent : do you call the judge, and his opponent was so confused that he just said well I don’t know in Polish so the judge couldn’t intervene. Anyways, that circus went one for about 1 minutes.<br />
<br />
So Adam (it’s his name) finally finished his games, we went directly to it.<br />
<br />
Round  3 : Adam the Polish guy.<br />
Anti Euro Meta v.s. Ranger Horn/ Moria with 4 trackers and that card that assigns an orc to an exhausted companion…<br />
<br />
I started talking a little to him, being friendly and all but that big bald guy with monobrow would just answer shortly with a strong polish accent to cut every discussion, so I set myself to plan B : mean game.<br />
<br />
Game 1 :<br />
He bid high but let me start. That surpised me since he was playing Moria and there is no way my 10 companion 6 stealths bounder 2 sting horn with legion of allies deck can loose against moria. So I was quite happy. I set myself to mov once each turn and it worked. I got a killer draw from the start, Elrond, Ottar and set up 3 armories at site 3! Thats a good sign usually. I Kept moving once and he kept trying to kill me but couldnt. So I was able to overwhelm him at site because of all my armories and scimitars which generated a very good early swarm. I like when you overwhelm your opponent while you are ahead. To my that’s a good sign of a deck working.<br />
<br />
So even if that game only went to site 4, it took a while since that guy kept thinking forever. I would have liked to see my croatian opponent from WorldCup day 2 playing against him J.<br />
<br />
Game 2 :<br />
He began I think and was able to set up real well : frying pan, rumil galadriel legolas aragorn’s bow and I didnt draw one elrond or ottar before site 8 so I figured I wouldnt overwhelm him that game so I began moving fast two. At one point I had the choice of double moving past site 6 sanctuary and began wondering about doing it or not. Then I asked myself, what site 7 could he be playing (since I had a few good allies setted up with horn) and then I looked at his face and it quickly became apparent that he was lpaying discard allies. Just by the little smile at the corner of his face, you could see that he wanted me to move. He even had his hand near his sites. So I had to plan my double move without my allies, I started thinking about it, saw his frying pan and rumil and Galadriel and thought : that will also penazile him. Since he also had elrond and calaghlin so I moved and was able to survive relatively easily but my opponent was so proud of playing his site and saying discard all your allies with his now apparent smile. Gotta hide your game better than this man. Anyways, he would be damaged at 7 and I would move to 8, looking at my deck and realizing that his frying pan would give him the game, so I had to double move. I had bounder and stealth in hand so Frodo would need 24 to be overwhelmed and I also had Sam which meant I could pass along the ring to him and stealth and bounder him as well. I also knew he was playing Tol Brandil but had only played 2 trackers. It was a very risky move, but there was no way I wuold stop him with frying pan on and no armories left so I tried it. He played a zillion minions including the troll but I was still alright until he played guard commander with like 10 left in the pool which meant game. He won the second one and that was my only loss of the day, my second in two days, theoratically my 5th of the week. I knew I woul dwin this matchup. During the game, I could have moved 4-6 but stopped at 5 for no reason, because I thought I could overwhelm him again so I went to the bathroom and thought about it. It would be pretty simple : if he got frying pan or is well equipped (rumil and bows) I start running, if not, I overwhelm.<br />
<br />
I had a chance to talk to Yannick and Yako between games and it was really cool since there began to be a lot of people watching our games since it was the semi-finals. I told Yannick I would win this one and he just said : I know, I don’t think you can loose another one today. Yannick just knows what to say to encourage someone. So I sat back to the table.<br />
<br />
Game 2 :<br />
I bid more to start and moved slowly at first. He did the same, not wanting to get ahead of me befor ehe was geared. The problem for him however was that I drew Elrond and Ottar that game and was able to set up another nice condition reserve. So I moved ahead unchallenged while he was reluctantly moving with Aragorn and Frodo with pan (gosh darnit pan). Then something interesting happened. When I moved to site 6 with boromir and horn and a zillion companions, he played Enquea and a lot of other stuff. I didnt want to loose Boromir so I had to find a way to keep him. So I began placing the minions in front of my guys saying : I’m just hinking and I kept thinking and assigning for a good amount of time, having him think about the assignments two, I was trying to get his focus on the assignments and it was working so after a while, I quickly said that’s it, I skip my manoeuver (as if it didn’t matter) and there it was, so focused on the forecoming assignements he said : me two! Alleluia and then with my smile he realised his mistake and said… but Enquea. So I looked at the judge who was sitting righ tnext to him and closely wacthing the game and I said judge? He said, the manoeuver has passed since both players skipped their manoeuver actions. I jubilated. The polish monobrow on the other hand kept switching between english and polish saying no but you don’t uderstand. His defence now was that he spoke english poorly when we had spoken quite a lot with him speaking english quite well. So when he saw that didnt work, he said, but in polish, when you say i skip, but, it’s like the same word, the same thing as saying I exert Enquea. So the judge was patiently listening to that non sense and called Scott who listened to that same lame defence and after a good 5 minutes of listening to him I asked the judge : what happens now and he professionally said : my ruling stays, the manoeuver phase is skipped. While Adam was trying to polish his way out of this I kept looking at Yako and Yannick and they were smiling cause we all knew Adam had just been had.<br />
<br />
For the rest of the game, he kept saying insults in polish to me and was even playing in polish. I knew he was deconcentrated, but I had to get him really out of his game. So I asked the judge if he could sepak in English so I could understand and the judge asked him to please talk in English. The fact of not being allowed to speak his own language looked to be very frustrating for him as his mono now said : anger. He moved to site 5 with Frodo and aragorn and my 3 armories and I played scout, trolls keyward and troll which killed him right away.<br />
<br />
I was on my way to the finals. For those of you who do not like the way I treated that Polish guy, I suggest you inform yourself of the way he went to win his match for 3rd place. As I said before, I got two modes : the nice one and the less nice one. That monobrow asked for B.<br />
<br />
The finals, however would be completely different, as I am happy to tell you that I met one of the best gentleman and fair player I know. We both played the game without any mind game and with fairness and I must say that it was a great relief and pleasure for me that it was so.<br />
<br />
Round 4 , the finals : Gabor Vida, the Gentleman.<br />
<br />
Anti Euro Meta v.s. Boromir Pippin Start but the uncommon boromir with Elrond Ottar and Card Drawing Gandlaf with sleeps and gear and… oh hell you can look at his deck from DGMA as it is as weird as it is efficient.<br />
<br />
The funny thing was that when the semi finals ended, the staff from the convention center began taking all the stuff away, like chairs and tables. They were taking the walls down and even the heating system went off so there we were, playing for the Premier serie, with the big check placed to my right, getto yoda leaning on it like the cool homie he is, Dan Bojanowski sitting next to me with his sweater because it’s so gosh darnit cold and only a few specators including Yannick, yako, Joel and The Gaffer who I all thank for staying to watch the game. To tell you, the mood was nothing but grandiose as we kept hearing tables slamming against the ground and drills and trucks.<br />
<br />
I already had a cold but with not heating system on in that big place, it was crazy, I kept coughing and I was so gosh darnit tired I once said : wait we got to do assignment when my opponent said : any manoeuver? At one point I was so sleeping that when a guy took a picture of my opponent’s swarm it just woke me up and helped me face it.<br />
<br />
My opponent on the other hand seemed concentrated and focused. I had seen his genuine smile when he beat his semi-finals opponent and  that guy just seemed to be a sincere and simple player. So I started plan A with him and it worked fine, we talked and laughed, he really was a nice guy.<br />
<br />
Game 1<br />
<br />
He thought a long time about how to bid and finally said 8 to my 1 (hey gotta bid something). So he went first as he judged it very important. He moved once and got geared early in the game with Elrond Ottar and Gandalf. He kept drawing his sleep caradhras exactly at the right time and kept having enough possessions to save his uncommon boromir (who kicks hiney againstmoria by the way) so he had like 7 companions with my no enquea. He was moving wuite easily, double moving 4-6 and 6-8. I, on the other hand was always stopped by his swarm since I resisted, but there was no way I was moving again with 7 minions on the table.<br />
<br />
So I quickly figured that the only way to beat him wat to overwhelm him. When he played frying pan on frodo at 6 my tired and sick brain began to see the end. However, I didn’t abandon. I started thinkin : I got da man. But i have no such a little thing. And the minions I had in my hand were the last ones in my deck (except for a scavenger) so when he moved to 7 I played conditions and reconciled but nothing else. Of course, he moved again and on my reconciliation I drew such a little thing, like I was supposed two (probabilities ar eon your side when theres 10 cards left in your draw deck with 2 such a little thing and you draw four). So I was able to play like 9 minions and kill Boromir in the manouever so he went down to 6 and I had Guard commander on with a zillion pool left. Before he had moved, I had seen a PATHS in his hand (to make things even worse) so I knew there was no point on putting more than one minion on Frodo. I setted up to overwhelm everyone else and I had just enough minions to do that. At some point I assigned all my minions to companions but being so tired and sick, I didnt see that there was a scavenger left from the other table (swarming takes space) so my opponent looked at me and gave me the scavenger saying : where does this one go?. By the look in his face, you knew that it wasnt because he was naif. I knew right then that being aware of the importance of thios minion, my opponent would conciently allow me to assign him in all fairness. Immediately I was amazed at that. I assigned it to gimli, which killed him and he genuienly had a displeased gesture, but accepting it. If that is not the example oeasterlingood sportsman, than I dont know what is. Finally, my swarm would kill everyone but Sam with the ring at site 8. He would move to site 9 with me having no minion left in my deck but having they are coming and 6 cards with relics of moria which allowed me to get a trolls keyward and moria scout with scimitar to avoid the paths. Quite franky, I don’t know where I pulled that one from.<br />
<br />
After the game I went to the bathroom and Yannick and yako came with me, they were more enthousiastic than I since I was so tired and sick but hearing made me enthousiast again and it was then that yannick said the simplest, but most intelligent thing : his boromir is killing you, if yuo dnt draw such a little thing in your oppening hand, mulligan. And that made sense, a lot of sense.<br />
<br />
So I got back to the table and I knew Yannick and Yako were watching closely as my oppening hand would prove to be the turning point of the game.<br />
<br />
Game 2<br />
<br />
I didnt draw such a little thing so I mulliganed. I didnt draw it again so he moved untouched to 2. Then I was able to move to 3 and I did it. It is then that I reconciled that precious card. I didnt show my hand to anyone and particularly took care in not showing my opponent anything about what I had drawn. I watched him play a possession with stress as he stoped playing things and said I moved. Even then I remained straight faced. I played an orc, he said archery, I said : shall we play manoeuver before, he said yes and there it was, I slammed the such a little thing on the table (since there is no other way to play a card that says : you have just lost your main companion on site 2) and after a grimace from him all we heard was a distant but loud : BLINK! BLINK!. I immediately started laughing as everyone looke din Yannick’s direction who said : I am sorry, I just couldnt stop myself. It was so funny. I didnt want to disrespect my opponent so I tried to stop laughing but every 10 seconds or more I just smiled.<br />
<br />
The rest of the game was as close as the first one. He kept moving with his gosh darnit frying pan and many companions, discarding my conditions everytime I had some with gosh darnit Sleep Caradhras so I was only able to stay one site ahead of him. On the other hand, every time I played a lot of companions,he would play Enquea (he played 3 of them) When I moved to 7, he played only one orc, that one that does like 10 different things. So I assigned him to whomever (my most powerfull companion was a 7 strenght, so I took one wound) and then I said reconcile but he said I have regroup action and that one little orc just exhausted my entire party cause of 3 wounds on frodo. He had one it, he had stopped me with only one orc. So I had to stop and he moved once to my very good welcome which damaged him a lot, but I had to kill aragorn to avoid him creating 3 archery next turn so I had to but 32 againt him since he had flaming brands and last alliance and since he put da man against him (good move). So Rumil, legolas, sam with frying pan and frodo with sting survived. Thats a lot of wounds to my little orcs when theres only like 15 cards in my draw pile. However, he had to stop cause there was a zillion minions left on the table.<br />
<br />
So there I moved to 8 after playing lots of companions and knowing he had another enquea but I wanted the double move and with legolas and callaghlin I knew he would play enquea, exert him and that would be one minion less for site 9. So he played the afformentionned Enquea and a good 4 orcs but prefered to kill exhausted sam and gandalf instead of all healed boromir with horn so I called Elrond and Ottar, Elrond killed an orc, legolas killed enquea in archery, other runners died to my companions until there were 3 orcs left. So I used callaghlin and there was one orc left. I tried to act like I was going to stop there, exerting callaghlin apparently anywhere, not caring about it. Then I said : I move. A lot of people were surprised at this but there was no way I would have stopped him with 2 minions left in my draw deck and his rumil+legolas+sam frying pas+frodo with sting.<br />
<br />
So there it was, another very very close push. Fortunately for me, at the start of the game I was inteligent enough to bid 0 because I had a feeling he was playing summit of amon hen so that didnt give him one more card. That would prove to be game breaking. Listen to that :<br />
<br />
I move with 5 companions, all of which are exhausted except Merry which is all clear. Frodo has Sting. Thats it. Theres is already one orc on the table. He has they are coming. He reconciles 5 cards. He tries to play as much scavengers as he can but seems to draw no more minions so he discards other cards to get scavengers until at one point there are 5 minions on the table and he has such a little thing, palanthir and another card in hand. The first ones are both game breaking since I have intuitions in hand and since Boromir is on the table, exhausted. However, he has a runner in play which means I can put a 6 and 5 strenght orc on Frodo and still survive. So, even if the Palanthir and such a little thing would damage me like mad they are worthless now. So he thinks about it for a good time and discards the three for a scavenger which puts a scimitar on the runner (very important) and draws on card. Oh how I looked at that card but he kept it in hand!<br />
<br />
So there it was, Frodo had 12 against him but I had one Stealth and one Intuition so I survived and immediately shook his hand. Yako just roared like when he wins in important games and I did the same as I shook their hands. Him, Yannick and Joel supported me all the time and I am very thankful for that. When you have the best big tournament player cheering for you, that helps.<br />
<br />
I told Gabor he totally deserved to finish so high and told him he honored the game, which I firmly believe. Then I hugged ghetto Yoda and took the check for a picture where I try to squeeze that huge thing in my pocket.<br />
<br />
Scott gave me an awesome ring (real gold) with Essen Champion 2002 written on it and the Hungarian I had beaten at the World Cup congratulated me, as did the other Hungarian and the Kaffer, who had stayed this long. Thanks man J. So there I went, so tired and sick, we took a cab back to the hotel, I ate and went to bed, having to wake up at 5 the next mourning to catch my flight.<br />
<br />
Crazy week. I loved every second of it. I hope my account of it has not been too boring (I know it’s a long one). That’s how I won Essen.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Props :<br />
-Ghetto Yoda, he’s my homie.<br />
-Yannick saying Blink Blink in the finals, hilarious.<br />
-Such a litte thing when everyone plays Boromir with horn.<br />
-Ulaire Nertea for being da man.<br />
-The Gaffer for having humongous balls playing with frodo alone.<br />
-That french speaking guy playing sauron who will never ask someone if they have manoeuver actions when he’s starting them J.<br />
-Rolan Benn for being a nice guy.<br />
-Bastian for not being intimidating for one second J<br />
-Yako for cheering for me.<br />
-Joel for always coming back to me and, when I ask about he did at a draft among the best players in the world says : I won like it’s normal. Might of Numenor all the WAY!!!<br />
-Benoit for being so funny and listening to what I have to say about the game, even if I didnt have a name before the tournament.<br />
-Gregory Denis for following me during day 1. I tell ya, he was the one stalking me.<br />
-Gabor Vida for being a genuienely fair player. Huge respect to you man.<br />
-Kyle Heuer for being really cool.<br />
-Dan Bojanowski for saying : I guess you got your bye into worlds back, knowing what it meant to me and how I told him I would.<br />
-Scott Gaeta for always being available to talk about the game and everything else.<br />
-A huge cardboard check for transforming what my relatives called a hobby that is going to far into a carefully planned investment (yeah right…).<br />
-My brother and Dave.<br />
<br />
Slops :<br />
-Unibrow for his work in general, but particularly in the match for 3rd place.<br />
-The convention workers for slamming tables at the ground while I’m playing my financial future.<br />
-That gosh darnit cold + no heating for making me say we gotta to do assignement before manoeuver and making me forget about a scavenger.<br />
<br />
Watch for us Quebecers at the World Cup and next year, we’re just starting to take this thing seriously J.<br />
<br />
See ya, <br />
<br />
Patrick Malboeuf<br />
